{"timestamp": "2025-12-06 22:52:56.953355", "event": "llm_end", "text": "Troubleshooting Diagnosis Report\n\nScope and intent checks\n- Network intent: User subnets 10.<core>.<dist>.0/24 should reach the server farm 10.200.0.0/24 (DNS/web frontends/load balancer). Backend web servers live on an isolated backend subnet (20.200.0.0/24) behind the load balancer and must not be reachable directly by hosts.\n- Control plane: OSPF distributes reachability for infrastructure and server farm networks end-to-end.\n\nSummary assessment\n- Overall network health: Normal. End-to-end connectivity, name resolution, and HTTP services perform as expected. OSPF routing is consistent with the topology. Backend isolation is enforced.\n- No service-impacting anomalies detected.\n- Minor observation: very short DHCP lease on a sample host (≈60 seconds), likely lab default; not causing issues.\n\nEvidence and findings\n\n1) Reachability and routing\n- Ping matrix (functions.get_reachability): Representative hosts and servers (e.g., host_1_1_1_1, host_2_1_1_1, web_server_0..3, dns_server, load_balancer) show 0% loss, RTT ~1.5–4 ms across subnets. No asymmetries or loss patterns observed.\n- Host sample (host_1_1_1_1):\n  - IP config: 10.1.1.12/24 via DHCP; default via 10.1.1.1; DNS 10.200.0.2 (verified in /etc/resolv.conf).\n  - Route table correct for local and default routes.\n- OSPF data:\n  - server_access_router: Has connected 10.200.0.0/24 and OSPF routes to all user subnets via 172.16.0.14 (eth7). OSPF neighbor is Full/Backup on eth7 (stable).\n  - router_dist_1_1 and router_dist_2_1: Have OSPF routes to 10.200.0.0/24 via core, and their local user subnets are connected. Metrics consistent with inter-area paths.\n  - Observation: server_access_router shows both C>* and an O line for 10.200.0.0/24; FIB selects connected. This is benign and not impacting.\n\n2) DNS and service discovery\n- DNS server (10.200.0.2) listening on TCP/UDP 53; reachable from hosts (ping 0% loss).\n- Resolution from host_1_1_1_1: web0.local -> 10.200.0.3; web1.local -> 10.200.0.4; web99.local -> 10.200.0.7. Name lookup times low (≈3–9 ms).\n\n3) HTTP services and load balancing\n- Frontend web servers (10.200.0.3–10.200.0.6) listening on TCP/80 (verified on web_server_0..3).\n- From hosts:\n  - HTTP to http://web0.local, http://web1.local, http://web2.local, http://web3.local returns 200 OK; TTFB ≈0.19–0.52 s; total ≈1.0–1.33 s for a ~256 KB page — expected for lab.\n  - HTTP to http://web99.local returns 200 OK with Nginx server header; similar timing profile.\n- Load balancer (10.200.0.7/24, 20.200.0.1/24):\n  - Nginx upstream configured to 20.200.0.2:80, 20.200.0.3:80, 20.200.0.4:80.\n  - LB reachability to backends verified: ICMP to 20.200.0.{2,3,4} OK; HTTP to those IPs OK with TTFB ≈0.25–0.41 s.\n  - LB default route via 10.200.0.1 (server_access_router) is present; listening on 0.0.0.0:80.\n\n4) Policy/segmentation validation (backend isolation)\n- From user host (host_1_1_1_1):\n  - ICMP to backend subnet (20.200.0.0/24) fails as expected: “Destination Net Unreachable” from the default gateway for 20.200.0.1, and no response for 20.200.0.2. HTTP direct to 20.200.0.2:80 times out. This matches the design that backends are not host-accessible.\n  - Access to the published VIP (web99.local -> 10.200.0.7) works normally.\n\nPotential anomalies checked and ruled out\n- OSPF reachability to server farm: present on both distribution routers; server_access_router peers stable.\n- DNS reachability/resolution: working; no delays or failures.\n- Web service availability: all frontends and the load balancer respond; no errors.\n- Backend exposure: verified inaccessible from host networks (by design).\n\nNoteworthy observations (non-blocking)\n- DHCP lease on host_1_1_1_1 shows very short remaining valid_lft (~59 s), indicative of a very short lease duration in the lab. No functional impact observed but unusual for production.\n\nConclusion\n- No anomalies affecting user-to-service connectivity, DNS resolution, HTTP delivery, or OSPF routing were found.\n- Backend isolation is enforced correctly; the load balancer is correctly proxying to 20.200.0.0/24 backends.\n- The network is operating within expected parameters for the provided design. No faulty devices identified; no root-cause issues present at this time.", "generation_info": {"finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 18052, "output_tokens": 4820, "total_tokens": 22872, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 18048}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 3584}}}
